From: Sun Yuechi <sunyuechi@iscas.ac.cn>
Subject: [PATCH] src/seastar: add initial RISC-V port

Rebased from the standalone seastar 25.05.0 patch onto ceph's
bundled seastar fork (ceph/seastar @ 36c62083, 2024-07-07).

The reactor.cc sigsegv_action hunk from the standalone patch is
dropped because this older fork's signal handler does not extract
the faulting PC from ucontext at all (the per-arch ip extraction
landed in scylladb/seastar after the fork point).

- cacheline: 64B (typical for current Linux-capable RV cores)
- memory: huge_page_size = 2 MiB on RV64 Linux
- spinlock: cpu_relax() emits the Zihintpause `pause` hint via raw
  encoding so older assemblers still build (NOP on cores without it)
- thread: .cfi_undefined ra so unwinders stop at thread bottoms

---
 src/seastar/include/seastar/core/cacheline.hh |  2 ++
 src/seastar/include/seastar/core/memory.hh    |  2 ++
 src/seastar/include/seastar/util/spinlock.hh  | 10 ++++++++++
 src/seastar/src/core/thread.cc                |  2 ++
 4 files changed, 16 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/seastar/include/seastar/core/cacheline.hh b/src/seastar/include/seastar/core/cacheline.hh
--- a/src/seastar/include/seastar/core/cacheline.hh
+++ b/src/seastar/include/seastar/core/cacheline.hh
@@ -40,6 +40,8 @@ constexpr size_t cache_line_size =
     128;
 #elif defined(__aarch64__)
     128; // from Linux, may vary among different microarchitetures?
+#elif defined(__riscv)
+    64; // typical for current Linux-capable RISC-V cores (SiFive U7x, T-Head C9xx, SG2042/SG2044)
 #else
 #error "cache_line_size not defined for this architecture"
 #endif
diff --git a/src/seastar/include/seastar/core/memory.hh b/src/seastar/include/seastar/core/memory.hh
--- a/src/seastar/include/seastar/core/memory.hh
+++ b/src/seastar/include/seastar/core/memory.hh
@@ -140,6 +140,8 @@ static constexpr size_t huge_page_size =
     1 << 21; // 2M
 #elif defined(__PPC__)
     1 << 24; // 16M
+#elif defined(__riscv)
+    1 << 21; // 2M (Sv39/Sv48 PMD leaf on RV64 Linux)
 #else
 #error "Huge page size is not defined for this architecture"
 #endif
diff --git a/src/seastar/include/seastar/util/spinlock.hh b/src/seastar/include/seastar/util/spinlock.hh
--- a/src/seastar/include/seastar/util/spinlock.hh
+++ b/src/seastar/include/seastar/util/spinlock.hh
@@ -67,6 +67,16 @@ inline void cpu_relax() {
     __asm__ volatile("yield");
 }
 
+#elif defined(__riscv)
+
+[[gnu::always_inline]]
+inline void cpu_relax() {
+    // Zihintpause `pause` hint, encoded directly so old assemblers without
+    // Zihintpause support still build. On cores that don't implement the hint
+    // it decodes as a NOP (it's `fence w, 0` with rd=x0).
+    __asm__ volatile(".insn i 0x0F, 0, x0, x0, 0x010");
+}
+
 #else
 
 [[gnu::always_inline]]
diff --git a/src/seastar/src/core/thread.cc b/src/seastar/src/core/thread.cc
--- a/src/seastar/src/core/thread.cc
+++ b/src/seastar/src/core/thread.cc
@@ -307,6 +307,8 @@ thread_context::main() {
     asm(".cfi_undefined x30");
 #elif defined(__s390x__)
     asm(".cfi_undefined %r14");
+#elif defined(__riscv)
+    asm(".cfi_undefined ra");
 #else
     #warning "Backtracing from seastar threads may be broken"
 #endif
